Class SAXDataExtraction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
      • cw_1201592.SAXDataExtraction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, org.xml.sax.DTDHandler, org.xml.sax.EntityResolver, org.xml.sax.ErrorHandler

    public class SAXDataExtraction
extends org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
    Processes the XML data and provides searchings for Web documents. Instances of this class store:
    • a vector of Article objects extracted from the XML file;
    • a hash table, whose key is a Tag object and value is a list of this Tag object's associated Article objects;
    • an Article object;
    • an Annotation object;
    • an Tag object and
    • a string used to represent the string between a pair of tags in the XML file.
    There are operations to extract data from the XML file and populate these information objects, to calculate the total number of articles in dataset, to calculate the total number of unique tags in the dataset, to count the number of tags used to annotate a particular article, to access all the tags and their count for one particular article, to count the number of times two tags co-occur in the dataset, to access all the bookmarks and tag count that are annotated with a given tag and suggest up to ten most frequently co-occuring tags with regard to the current tag.
    Author:
    Boqing Liu
